
### **B. Ensure `.gitignore` is Properly Configured**

Create a `.gitignore` file to exclude sensitive data and unnecessary files from being pushed to GitHub.

**`.gitignore`:**

```gitignore
# Python compiled files
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Data directories
saved_responses/
cleaned_data/

# Environment files
.env

# Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Postman Collection (if not ready to be shared)
Content/Postman_Collection/postman_collection.json

# Logs
app.log
